comments: Robinson (NYK) is already in Tatum's (BOS) path when marginal body contact occurs as Tatum moves up the lane.
Barrett (NYK) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another as they move up the lane.

Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Fournier's (NYK) path and does not deliver the contact as the switch takes place. Tatum and Fournier briefly engage and disengage thereafter.
Fournier (NYK) brings his left arm down and initiates contact with Tatum's (BOS) left arm after his gather.
Schroder (BOS) briefly has his left arm around Randle's (NYK) midsection before quickly sliding it off.
Schroder (BOS) brings his arm down and some contact occurs with Quickley's (NYK) right arm after Quickley picks up his dribble. The contact is marginal.
Fournier (NYK) engages and disengages with Smart (BOS) following the inbound.
Smart (BOS) makes contact with the ball and the part of Fournier's (NYK) hand that is on the ball as he jumps behind Fournier along the perimeter.
Robinson (NYK) brings his left forearm toward Tatum's (BOS) back and marginal contact occurs as they each attempt to obtain rebounding position.
Tatum (BOS) brings his left hand toward Robinson's (NYK) front and marginal contact occurs as Robinson elevates for the rebound.
Brown (BOS) and Robinson (NYK) each make clean contact with the ball and Brown bats it away from Robinson during rebounding.
Brown (BOS) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Barrett (NYK) and Brown (BOS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Robinson (NYK) establishes a wide screening position and some leg-to-leg contact occurs with Brown (BOS) as the switch takes place. The contact is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) brings his left hand toward Barrett's (NYK) front and marginal contact occurs as Barrett fades away from the lane to make the pass.
Schroder (BOS) brings both hands toward Robinson's (NYK) back and marginal contact occurs as Robinson elevates to receive the pass.

Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Fournier's (NYK) path and does not deliver the contact as the switch takes place. Tatum and Fournier briefly engage and disengage thereafter.
Quickley (NYK) avoids making contact with Smart (BOS) and legally contests his jump shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) makes fingertip contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Fournier (NYK) before incidental contact occurs to Fournier's front.
After the ball becomes loose, Smart (BOS) brushes Fournier's (NYK) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Fournier simultaneously bobbles the ball toward the sideline.
Tatum (BOS) is moving forward toward the sideline and marginal contact occurs with Barrett's (NYK) left side after Barrett retrieves the loose ball.
Williams III (BOS) jumps vertically and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs with Barrett (NYK) after Barrett passes the ball.
Brown (BOS) re-establishes his screening position slightly and does not deliver the contact as Quickley (NYK) goes under.
Quickley (NYK) brings his hands toward Schroder's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs to Schroder's front as he turns the corner during the drive.
Quickley (NYK) is retreating alongside Schroder's (BOS) path and marginal body contact occurs before Schroder loses his balance inside the lane.
Schroder (BOS) gathers the ball with both hands and resumes his dribble in the lane.
Robinson (NYK) establishes a legal guarding position in Schroder's (BOS) path and absorbs the body contact that occurs before cleanly dislodging the ball away from Schroder.
Smart (BOS) brings his left arm toward Randle's (NYK) upper half and marginal contact occurs after Randle picks up his dribble.
Tatum (BOS) moves forward and initiates body and arm contact with Barrett during his upward shooting motion.

Randle (NYK) and Brown (BOS) engage with one another following the release of the free throw and marginal contact occurs before Brown trips over his teammate's foot. Any contact thereafter is deemed incidental.
Burks (NYK) extends his right forearm and initiates contact with Smart's (BOS) upper half during the drive. Any contact thereafter is deemed immaterial.
Schroder (BOS) engages and disengages with Quickley (NYK) during the inbound.
Brown (BOS) and Randle (NYK) engage with one another and as Brown trips over his own feet, marginal contact occurs to Randle's upper half as he retrieves the inbound.
Smart (BOS) commits a take foul on Randle (NYK).
Robinson (NYK) swipes from behind and cleanly dislodges Tatum (BOS) of the ball before any incidental contact occurs.
Burks' (NYK) right foot is out of bounds when he makes contact with the ball.
Schroder (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Barrett's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact.
Tatum (BOS) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Tatum (BOS) brings his off-arm toward Barrett's (NYK) side and marginal contact occurs as Tatum releases away at the end of the drive.
Tatum (BOS) engages and disengages with Quickley (NYK) during the inbound.

Tatum (BOS) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Barrett's (NYK) left wrist after the release. After communicating with the Replay Center, the on-court ruling of a successful three-point basket before the expiration of the game clock is confirmed.
